\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 3. What it's capable of
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \
\
  Confirmed working capabilities:\
\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 End-to-end pipeline
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 init-feature \uc0\u8594  plan \u8594  design \u8594  breakdown \u8594  execute \u8594  PR\cf2 \cb3 , each as a discrete skill with stage\
  files.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Per-feature state machine
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 loop_state.json\cf2 \cb3  schema (\cf12 \cb3 .claude/loop_state.json\cf2 \cb3 ), atomic transitions via\
  \cf12 \cb3 gate_transition.py\cf2 \cb3  (file-locked), validation via \cf12 \cb3 state_manager.py\cf2 \cb3 .\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Tier-aware workflows
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 xs/s/m/l\cf2 \cb3  configs in \cf12 \cb3 .claude/workflows/\cf2 \cb3  drive artifact depth, review requirements, escalation\
  thresholds.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Multi-route
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 feature / hotfix / epic / spike, each routed to a tailored stage list.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Resume + revision
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 every skill auto-detects partial state; \cf12 \cb3 /reopen\cf2 \cb3  cascades downstream "STALE" markers.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Subagent isolation enforcement
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 pre_spawn_validation.py\cf2 \cb3  hook blocks impl-path leaks into review/QA prompts (real,\
  tested).\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Secret + SAST scanning
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 secret_scanner.py\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 security_prescan.py\cf2 \cb3 , plus pre-write hook (\cf12 \cb3 write_guard.py\cf2 \cb3 ).\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Per-story failure ledger
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 failure_ledger.py\cf2 \cb3  prevents repeating broken approaches across retries.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Self-learning loop
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 retrospect\cf2 \cb3  skill spawns \cf12 \cb3 retrospective-analyst\cf2 \cb3  with run-log + loop_state only, auto-applies\
  \cf12 \cb3 agent_memory\cf2 \cb3  + \cf12 \cb3 pipeline_learning\cf2 \cb3  entries, routes \cf12 \cb3 config\cf2 \cb3 /\cf12 \cb3 workflow\cf2 \cb3  proposals to human queue.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Multi-repo, multi-module awareness
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 setup-env\cf2 \cb3  scans Maven/Gradle/npm/Go/Python/.NET, writes \cf12 \cb3 repo-registry.yml\cf2 \cb3 .\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Jira + Confluence MCP integration
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 jira-ops\cf2 \cb3  skill, MCP fallback to manual, \cf12 \cb3 input_extractor.py\cf2 \cb3  parses Confluence\
  storage HTML.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Atomic agent-memory updates
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 update_agent_memory.py\cf2 \cb3  with dedup (\uc0\u8805 0.60 word overlap), 200-line cap, .bak backup.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Diff-scoped reviews
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \'97 \cf12 \cb3 review-agent\cf2 \cb3  enforces diff-only rule; standalone \cf12 \cb3 /review-pr\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 /review-branch\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 /review-tdd\cf2 \cb3 \
  exist.\
\
  Areas claimed but thin:\
  - "Token budget" enforcement \'97 \cf12 \cb3 skill_setup.py\cf2 \cb3  resolves budgets, but no script actually enforces them at runtime;\
  budgets are passed as guidance to agents.\
  - "Monitoring" / \cf12 \cb3 skill_tracking.enabled\cf2 \cb3  \'97 config exists, no consumer.\
\
  
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 4. Greenfield vs legacy / existing codebase
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \
\
  Today's design is biased toward 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 existing codebases
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3 :\
\
  - \cf12 \cb3 codebase-analyst.md:67\cf2 \cb3  explicitly handles \cf12 \cb3 "no matches \'97 greenfield for this repo"\cf2 \cb3  and just reports it \'97 but the\
  pipeline assumes downstream stages still have a repo to point at.\
  - \cf12 \cb3 init-feature\cf2 \cb3  Q2 mandates repo + module selection from an existing \cf12 \cb3 projects.\{slug\}.root\cf2 \cb3  \'97 there's no greenfield\
  branch ("create a new repo for this feature").\
  - \cf12 \cb3 developer.md:36\cf2 \cb3  requires \cf12 \cb3 reference_branch\cf2 \cb3  for convention discovery; default \cf12 \cb3 main\cf2 \cb3 . Without an existing branch this\
  becomes a no-op and the agent will invent conventions.\
  - \cf12 \cb3 setup-env\cf2 \cb3  cannot scan a project whose \cf12 \cb3 root\cf2 \cb3  directory doesn't exist (it warns and skips per SKILL line\'a035).\
  - Legacy is well-supported: lower \cf12 \cb3 coverage_threshold\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 legacy-app\cf2 \cb3  sample project with \cf12 \cb3 jira_push: false\cf2 \cb3 ,\
  \cf12 \cb3 reference_branch\cf2 \cb3  per repo, codebase-analyst signature/call-chain reading.\
\
  
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Verdict:
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  strong for legacy/brownfield; weak for from-scratch greenfield. Adding a \cf12 \cb3 route: greenfield\cf2 \cb3  (or\
  \cf12 \cb3 repos.bootstrap: true\cf2 \cb3 ) would let \cf12 \cb3 init-feature\cf2 \cb3  skip repo selection and \cf12 \cb3 setup-env\cf2 \cb3  to scaffold a new repo rather than\
  scan one.\
  \
  
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 5. Language / tool / framework independence
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \
\
  Mostly stack-agnostic, with a Java/Maven bias in some defaults:\
\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Build detection
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  (\cf12 \cb3 setup-env\cf2 \cb3  Steps 2\'964): Maven, Gradle, npm, Go, Python, .NET \'97 all first-class.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Test/build invocation
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  is recorded per-module (\cf12 \cb3 build_cmd\cf2 \cb3 ) and passed to \cf12 \cb3 developer\cf2 \cb3  / \cf12 \cb3 qa-engineer\cf2 \cb3  \'97 no hardcoded\
  language assumption at runtime.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf12 \cb3 pre_spawn_validation.py:67
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  matches \cf12 \cb3 .(java|ts|tsx|go|py|js|jsx|rb|rs|c|cpp|h)\cf2 \cb3  \'97 broad but missing Kotlin, Swift,\
  Scala, PHP, C#/.cs.\
  - \cf12 \cb3 analyze_complexity.py\cf2 \cb3  and \cf12 \cb3 diff_review_filter.py\cf2 \cb3  look at file extensions \'97 quick check needed for breadth.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Settings.json
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  \cf12 \cb3 permissions.allow\cf2 \cb3  is heavy on JVM (\cf12 \cb3 mvn\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 mvnw\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 gradle\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 gradlew\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 java\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 javac\cf2 \cb3 ) plus \cf12 \cb3 npm\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 node\cf2 \cb3 . No \cf12 \cb3 cargo\cf2 \cb3 ,\
  \cf12 \cb3 go\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 dotnet\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 python -m pytest\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 bundle\cf2 \cb3 , \cf12 \cb3 composer\cf2 \cb3 . Users on those stacks must add permissions.\
