\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 7. Learnings
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \
\
  What HeadMaster does well:\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Strict isolation contracts
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  (\cf12 \cb3 pre_spawn_validation.py\cf2 \cb3  is real, not just documentation).\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Atomic state writes
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  with \cf12 \cb3 file_lock.py\cf2 \cb3 ; backup-and-restore via \cf12 \cb3 gate_transition.py rollback\cf2 \cb3 .\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Distillation chain enforced
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  (PRD \uc0\u8594  TDD \u8594  Stories; CLAUDE.md "Context Discipline").\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Failure ledger
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  prevents the "same broken retry" anti-pattern.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Human gates are unconditional
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  for high-blast-radius items (Jira push, PR merge, pipeline edits).\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 MCP first, manual fallback
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  for Jira \'97 no hard dependency. \
  \
  Architectural tensions:\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Two states of truth
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  for which agents/skills exist (filesystem, README, CLAUDE.md) \'97 drift already happened\
  (retrospect, retrospective-analyst).\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Sample vs README
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  for \cf12 \cb3 config.yml\cf2 \cb3  show two different schemas \'97 onboarding ambiguity.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf12 \cb3 /scan\cf6 , \cf12 /commit\cf6 , \cf12 /handoff
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  live in \cf12 \cb3 commands/\cf2 \cb3  (slash commands), while peer functionality lives in \cf12 \cb3 skills/\cf2 \cb3  \'97 the\
  boundary is unclear to users.\
  - 
\f1\b \cf6 \cb3 Phase D and Phase E
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb3  are mentioned in best-practices (README:884) but the execute pipeline implements only A/B/C \'97\
  terminology debt.\
